20/01/2006
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- A plane crash has claimed the lives of more than 40 Slovak soldiers and crewmembers on their way back from Kosovo. The troops had served with KFOR and were returning to Slovakia when their An-24 plane went down Thursday (19 January) evening in a mountainous area in Hungary. Authorities report one survivor. There were conflicting reports about the number of people on board the aircraft, with various officials quoting figures between 40 and 45. (AP, Reuters, BBC, AFP, CNN - 20/01/06)
